<H1>Structure of the file system</H1>

<P>The UNIX file system is organised as a hierarchy of
 <A HREF="opfile2.html">directories</A>
 starting from a single directory called <EM>root</EM>
which is represented by a <STRONG>/</STRONG> (slash). Imagine it as
being similar to the root system of a plant or as an inverted
tree structure.</P>

<P>Immediately below the root directory are several system
directories that contain information required by the
operating system. The file holding the UNIX 
 <A HREF="kernel.html">kernel</A> is also here.</P>

